HEADWORD: Portland vase
<hw>Port"land vase`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A celebrated cinerary urn or
vase found in the tomb of the Emperor Alexander Severus. It is owned by
the Duke of Portland, and kept in the British Museum.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

